 plus extra for frying","500 g turkey mince","1 tsp dried oregano","20 g water","40 g tomato sauce, plus extra to serve (see Tips)","½ tsp salt","1 pinch ground black pepper","12 slider buns (or small bread rolls)","iceberg lettuce, shredded (optional)","cheese, sliced (optional)"]}],"id":"r138801","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-WNhLinKAkf4\/XZQHyPkeNII\/AAAAAAAAcMI\/SvmwX01iO24AJ7Tg_AjRNxz1YyLDbg4uQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_quFseROBcJDfDr_G.png","title":"Sliders with sunflower sauce","publishedAt":"2017-10-16T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"16 g","fat":"10.1 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"7 g","calories":"778 kJ \/ 185 kcal"},"usefulItems":"small bowl , plastic wrap, bowl, non-stick frying pan, thermal serving bowl or plate, refrigerator, stove top","hintsAndTricks":["To make your own tomato sauce, please refer to the recipe in <em>The Basic Cookbook<\/em> or <em>Everyday Cookbook<\/em>.","Sunflower sauce and turkey patties can be made a day in advance. Store in the refrigerator until ready to pan fry and serve."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","40m","12 portions"]}